    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is for production code yes. This is for cases where I want to use local daemons on the same system using CN to identify what function they are serving. For example: Imagine I have a \"password\" daemon, it would have CN=password and I would connect to \"localhost\".\n\nIf for any reason you need to connect to a server without using DNS (for dependency reasons, alternative discovery services or whatnot) you would also need this feature.\n\nEDIT: It's also quite essential for SSL over Unix sockets - how bizarre that might sound, it does have its uses.\n"
  },
